8:
Master, your liver's gonna give out if
ya keep drinking so much!
11:
These memories had to come back
now, of all times...
22:
You're not serious about never
coming back here again... are you?
26:
I've grown tired of your sake and
food. I have no more business with
you.
30:
But that's no reason to say you'll
NEVER come back, is it?
34:
...You keep forgetting this fact, but
let me remind you—I am a tengu.
37:
I follow my whims. This is where this
one ends.
41: Oh. I'm sorry, am I interrupting?
45: Er... I think we just finished.
49:
Well, that works out for me. May I
steal a moment of your time?
56:
Hyakki Yagyo—a night where a ton
of yokai come out...
60:
Indeed. It is easy for spiritual energy
to stagnate in places with water.
That's where you'll find yokai being
born from Orochi's malevolent spirit.
63:
They are devoid of their own free
will—more like rabid beasts that
attack any and all.
68:
With their numbers, you cannot
ignore the threat they pose. That is
where we come in, I assume?
72:
Dispersing the stagnation will take
everything we have. We simply do
not possess enough manpower.
76:
As much as it pains me, I must ask if
you'd be willing to handle the yokai.
96:
Oh, come on! You've gotta be
kidding me!
101:
The nearby villages wouldn't stand a
chance against these numbers...
106:
We'll just have to make sure it
doesn't come to that!
111:
Should've run while they had the
chance. Those fools never learn...
121:
...Brats always bite off more than
they can chew!
142: You DARE stand in my way?
155: We should offer him our support!
166:
You're made of tougher stuff than 
I thought.
174:
...Don't need your thanks. This was
for me.
177:
Couldn't think of any other way to let
go of my past otherwise.
180: ...This is goodbye. I mean it this time.
187:
If the mood strikes you, you're
welcome back anytime. I'll set aside
some good sake for you.
192:
That old man just flew off without
saying anything... Wonder if he really
plans on never coming back.
196:
Who knows? He might drop by
unexpectedly sometime.
203:
You're late. Did you make a pit stop
somewhere?
218:
You said you'd treat me to good
food and sake.
221:
But these dishes are mediocre, and
this sake tastes rotten.
225:
That's my lunch... And you're drinking
my cooking sake...
229: Are you saying this is my fault?
232:
Normally, I'd give you thrashing for
that... but I'm in a good mood today.
235:
Bring me your finest sake as an
apology.
239:
...Until you do, I'll be waiting in this
village of yours.
243:
You're just gonna decide that on
your own, huh...
247:
Of course. I'm a tengu. I decide
things on a whim.
